						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>First four lines are damaged. This Kannada inscription is in characters of the eighth century A.D. It records the death of a hero named Rā[ma], a servant of <hi rend="italic">Taḷigai taḷāra</hi> (Police official), who fought with an elephant of Vallabha and killed it. The event took place during the reign of Chāṟu-arasa, probably the king Chāṟuponnera-arasa of the Noḷamba-Pallava dynasty.</p>						

						</summary>
